annotationA: GPI mannosyltransferase 2; Mannosyltransferase involved in glycosylphosphatidylinositol-anchor biosynthesis. Transfers the second mannose to the glycosylphosphatidylinositol during GPI precursor assembly. Required for the GPI-mediated endoplasmic reticulum exit and proper targeting to the cell surface of chp. Required for GPI-mediated membrane attachment of chp, qsm and Cont. Essential for microvillar stability in the rhabdomere; Belongs to the PIGV family
annotationB: CG2292; Transferase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: GPI anchor biosynthetic process
